Hello, and welcome to my Medium profile!

I’m Harshal Kukade, a **QA Lead and Penetration Team Lead **with over a decade of experience in the cybersecurity domain. My expertise spans web applications, APIs, Android, iOS, IoT, system, and network penetration testing, as well as threat modeling to identify and mitigate risks effectively.

Throughout my career, I’ve honed my skills using industry-standard tools and technologies like Burp Suite, Nessus, Nmap, Wireshark, Postman, Metasploit Framework, SonarQube, and many more. My journey has also led me to dive deep into cyber forensics, Python-based automation, and Security Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) to create robust and scalable security solutions.
I’ve been privileged to work with esteemed clients like Huawei, Philips, Honda, BMW, Trustonics, and India's top Law Enforcement Agencies (LEA), delivering impactful solutions to safeguard their systems and data. These experiences have enriched my understanding of diverse cybersecurity challenges and taught me how to manage projects that contribute to organizational growth and enhance global cybersecurity standards.
I’m certified as a CEH, OSCP, CHFI, and CSA professional, which complements my hands-on experience in building secure infrastructures and ensuring compliance with the highest industry standards.
Feel free to connect with me on LinkedIn or check out my projects and scripts on GitHub. Through this platform, I aim to share my insights on penetration testing, automation, and cybersecurity trends, helping others navigate the evolving digital landscape.
I’m passionate about mentoring and empowering the next generation of cybersecurity professionals. Currently, Harshal is leading penetration testing efforts at LeewayHertz Technology.
Thank you for stopping by, and stay tuned for more articles on cutting-edge security practices!
